<subSubSection id="C35D656A5551FE31FF72FD42FC2EFC0A" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF836E15551FE31FF72FD42FDDEFCEA" blockId="18.[178,1085,752,832]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">
C o m m e n t: The previously known distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D625551FE31FD2AFD42FC8EFCAF" baseAuthorityName="EPPELSHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[746,865,752,773]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudocalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis id="B933EAF35551FE31FD2AFD42FC8EFCAF" box="[746,865,752,773]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">P. angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ranged from 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FC2DFD42FBD2FCAC" box="[1005,1085,752,774]" name="Albania" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Albania</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FF1DFCBFFEC8FC89" box="[221,295,781,803]" name="Croatia" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Croatia</collectingCountry>
across 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FEB4FCBFFE53FC88" box="[372,444,781,802]" name="Greece" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Greece</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FE1CFCBFFDCAFC89" box="[476,549,781,803]" name="Turkey" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD64B105551FE31FDF3FCBFFD53FC88" author="ASSING V" box="[563,700,781,802]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197" pagination="3 - 8" refId="ref16235" refString="ASSING V. (2000): A revision of the species of Euryalea MULSANT &amp; REY and Pseudocalea LUZE (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). Supplement I. - Entomologische Blatter 96 (1): 3 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">ASSING 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD64B105551FE31FD06FCBFFCE9FC88" author="ASSING V" box="[710,774,781,802]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197" pagination="177 - 209" refId="ref16703" refString="ASSING V. (2007 c): On the Aleocharini of Turkey, with notes on some species from adjacent regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 57 (1): 177 - 209." type="journal article" year="2007">2007c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD64B105551FE31FCD1FCBFFCBCFC89" author="ASSING V" box="[785,851,781,803]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197" pagination="117 - 172" refId="ref16834" refString="ASSING V. (2009 a): On the Staphylinidae of Turkey. VI. Thirteen new species and additional records (Coleoptera). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 79: 117 - 172." type="journal article" year="2009">2009a</bibRefCitation>
). The above specimens represent the first records from 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FE32FC98FDC2FCEA" box="[498,557,810,832]" name="Israel" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Israel</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E15551FE31FF72FCE2FC2EFC0A" blockId="18.[178,1085,848,928]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">
The aedeagus of this species, in particular the shape of the ventral process, and the coloration are subject to some intraspecific variation. In contrast to material seen from 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FF72FC38FF15FC35" box="[178,250,906,927]" name="Greece" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Greece</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FEEBFC38FE98FC0A" box="[299,375,906,928]" name="Turkey" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, most of the specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F35076715551FE31FD5FFC38FD38FC0A" box="[671,727,906,928]" name="Israel" pageId="18" pageNumber="1197">Israel</collectingCountry>
have dark-brown legs.
</paragraph>
